Word	Definition
51% Attack, Majority Hash Rate Attack	When a single entity controls over 51% of the network's hash rate
Denominations	Common units and values used in the Bitcoin system like BTC, mBTC, uBTC
Txid, Transaction Identifier	Unique hash that identifies each transaction
Outpoint	Combination of transaction hash and output index that uniquely identifies an unspent output
Output, Transaction Output, TxOut	Amounts of BTC sent to addresses in a transaction
HD Wallet Seed, Root Seed	Master seed used to generate all keys in an HD wallet
Master Chain Code And Private Key	Values used to derive child keys in a HD wallet
Chain Code, HD Wallet Chain Code	Value chained to keys to strengthen child key derivation security
Child Key, HD Wallet Child Key	Keys derived from parent keys using Chain Code & Child Number
Wallet	Program that stores private keys and interacts with the blockchain
HD Protocol, HD Wallet, BIP32	Hierarchical Deterministic wallet standard
Parent Key, HD Wallet Parent Key	Key from which child keys are derived
Private Key, ECDSA Private Key	Random number used to sign transactions
Public Key, ECDSA Public Key	Value derived from private key used to receive funds
Signature, ECDSA Signature	Value proving ownership of funds signed with private key
Signature Script, ScriptSig	Part of transaction input validating signatures
Pubkey Script, ScriptPubKey	Part of transaction output defining payout conditions
Difficulty, Network Difficulty	Measure of how hard it is to find a valid block hash
nBits, Target Threshold	Compact representation of target threshold in block header
Proof Of Work	Method of validating transactions through resource expenditure
Block Header	Block identifier present in each block
Block, Block Of Transactions	Collection of valid transactions batched together
Confirmation Score, Confirmed Transaction	Measure of reliability based on number of blocks after it
Locktime, nLockTime	Timestamp or block height after which a tx can be included in a block
Sequence Number (Transactions)	Field used in replacement and relative locktimes of transactions
Input, Transaction Input, TxIn	Reference to previous output being spent including scriptSig
Redeem Script, RedeemScript	Script in a P2SH output defining validity conditions
P2PKH Address, Pay To PubKey Hash	Address format using hash of public key
M-of-N Multisig, Multisig Output	Output requiring M signatures from N available public keys
Opcode	Code inside scripts determining validity evaluation logic
Standard Transaction	Tx with valid signatures and outputs without uncommon features
P2SH Multisig, P2SH Multisig Output	Multisig using P2SH format
P2SH Address, Pay To Script Hash	Address format using hash of script instead of pubkey
Base58check, Bitcoin Address Encoding	Encoding validation of address strings
Payment Addresses	Addresses receiving payments starting with 1 or 3
Header Chain, Best Header Chain	Candidate chain of block headers
Mining, Miner	Process of validating transactions and adding them to the blockchain
High-Priority Transaction, Free Tx	Transactions without fees that are "free"
Minimum Relay Fee	Lowest network fee for nodes to propagate tx
Transaction Fee, Miner Fee	Amount in satoshis per KB paid to miners
Block Reward, Block Miner Reward	New coins "minted" and granted to the miner of a block
Coinbase, Coinbase Field	Special first transaction in each block
Coinbase / Generation Transaction	Transaction spending reward to the coinbase address
Genesis Block, Block 0	Very first block of the blockchain with no previous ones
Block Chain Height, Block Height	Height of the blockchain measured by number of blocks
Headers-First, Headers-First Sync	Faster sync by validating headers first before blocks
Blocks-First, Blocks-First Sync	Original and slower sync by validating blocks first
SPV, Simplified Payment Verification	Lightweight validation of blocks without full blockchain
Merkle Root	Top hash in Merkle tree representing all tx hashes in a block
Merkle Tree	Tree structure used to efficiently summarize all tx in a block
Merkle Block	Block including Merkle tree allowing verification of transactions
Bloom Filter	Probabilistic data structure used in SPV and mining alerts
Change, Change Address, Change Output	Remaining balance from a transaction sent to a new address
CompactSize Unsigned Integer	Variable length encoding of integers
Compressed Public Key	Form of serialized public keys to reduce size
Consensus Rules, Validation Rules	Rules defining valid block and transaction structure
Consensus	Global agreement on the valid blockchain and state
Unspent Transaction Output, UTXO	Unspent outputs in the UTXO set able to be spent
Null Data (OP_RETURN) Transaction	Transaction including arbitrary data in OP_RETURN script
DNS Seed	Seed nodes listed in source code seeding initial network nodes
Double Spend	Invalid scenario where a coin is spent twice
Escrow Contract	Script for conditionally locking funds until a set of rules are met
Extended Key, HD Wallet Extended Key	Master key exposing full public key tree of a HD wallet
Soft Fork, Soft-Forking Change	Change backward compatible still enforcing new structural rules
Hard Fork, Hard-Forking Change	Change not backward compatible, creates bifurcated blockchains
Fork, Accidental Fork	Potential result of incompatible changes to consensus rules
Hardened Extended Key (HD Wallets)	Extended keys tightened for security with separation of purpose
Initial Block Download, IBD	Process of syncing blockchain for the first time
Serialized Block, Raw Block	Binary representation of block for communication
Serialized Transaction, Raw Transaction	Binary representation of transaction for network transmission
RPC Byte Order	Byte ordering used in command line communication over JSON-RPC
Internal Byte Order	Endian ordering used internally in protocols
Inventory, Block Or Transaction Inventory	Messages announcing availability of data to download
Regtest, Regression Test Mode	Chain with configurable difficulty for testing
Testnet, Testing Network	Development version used to test apps with dispensable coins
Mainnet, Bitcoin Main Network	Primary live Bitcoin production network
Message Header	Specifying type and length of following payload in P2P protocol
Start String, Network Magic	Identifier of network in message headers
Stale Block	Valid block but not on best known chain due to a reorganization
Orphan Block	Block whose parent not known to node, temporarily stored
Payment Protocol, Payment Request, BIP70	Standard for communicating payment details to wallets
SIGHASH_ALL	Signature mode including all outputs in hash
Transaction Malleability, Mutability	Potential for transaction IDs to change
Signature Hash	Hash of transaction components signed in signature
SIGHASH_SINGLE	Signature covers all inputs and only output at same index
SIGHASH_ANYONECANPAY	Signature covers all outputs but allow change in inputs
SIGHASH_NONE	Signature covers no inputs and allows modification of outputs
Wallet Import Format	Standard for importing private keys into wallets
Watch-Only Address	Addresses without private keys for monitoring balances
Block Chain	Structure recording every valid bitcoin transaction that has occurred
